[%# WorkShops Implementation Phases - Database-Driven Containers %]
[%# This file is included in Planning.tt %]

<h4>🏗️ Implementation Phases (Database-Driven Containers)</h4>
<p><em>Each phase is a sub-project in the database with detailed todos. Click to expand/collapse phase details. Sub-project IDs: 174-182 (~50 todos total).</em></p>

[% TRY %]
    [% SET schema = c.model('DBEncy').schema %]
    
    <!-- Phase 0: Planning System Integration -->
    [% SET phase0 = schema.resultset('Project').find(174) %]
    [% IF phase0 %]
    <details class="phase-container" style="margin: 15px 0; border: 2px solid #4CAF50; padding: 10px; background: #e8f5e9;">
        <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.1em;">
            [% IF phase0.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSIF phase0.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
            Phase 0: Planning System Integration (PREREQUISITE - [% phase0.status %])
        </summary>
        <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <p><strong>What:</strong> Integrate WorkShops system into Planning.tt documentation. Establish foundation for all subsequent development work.</p>
            <p><strong>Why:</strong> Without proper planning documentation, the project lacks visibility, tracking, and integration with the overall system planning workflow. This phase establishes the foundation for all subsequent work by creating comprehensive planning documentation, linking to Project ID 8, documenting all 8 phases, and adding port 4004 access to the Overview section.</p>
            <p><strong>⚠️ Blocking Note:</strong> NO OTHER WORK proceeds until this phase is marked complete. This is a PREREQUISITE for all implementation phases.</p>
            
            <div style="margin: 10px 0; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background: white;">
                <h5>📊 Database Project Details</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Project ID:</strong> [% phase0.id %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Status:</strong> [% phase0.status %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> [% phase0.start_date %] → [% phase0.end_date %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Estimated Hours:</strong> [% phase0.estimated_man_hours %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Project Code:</strong> [% phase0.project_code %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Description:</strong> [% phase0.description %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Comments:</strong> [% phase0.comments %]</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <a href="/project/details?project_id=[% phase0.id %]" target="_blank">View Details</a> |
                    <a href="/project/editproject?project_id=[% phase0.id %]" target="_blank">Edit</a> |
                    <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase0.id %]" target="_blank">Add Todo</a>
                </p>
                
                [% SET phase0_todos = phase0.todos.search({}, { order_by => 'sort_order' }) %]
                [% IF phase0_todos.count > 0 %]
                    <h6>📋 Todos ([% phase0_todos.count %]):</h6>
                    <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                        [% FOREACH task IN phase0_todos.all %]
                            <li style="margin: 5px 0; padding: 5px; border-left: 2px solid #4CAF50; background: #fafafa;">
                                [% IF task.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSIF task.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
                                [% task.subject %]
                                <br><small>Status: [% task.status %] | Due: [% task.due_date %]</small>
                                <br><a href="/todo/showtodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">View</a> |
                                <a href="/todo/edittodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">Edit</a>
                            </li>
                        [% END %]
                    </ul>
                [% ELSE %]
                    <p><em>No todos. <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase0.id %]">Add a todo</a></em></p>
                [% END %]
            </div>
        </div>
    </details>
    [% END %]
    
    <!-- Phase 1: Database Schema & Models -->
    [% SET phase1 = schema.resultset('Project').find(175) %]
    [% IF phase1 %]
    <details class="phase-container" style="margin: 15px 0; border: 2px solid #FF9800; padding: 10px; background: #fff3e0;">
        <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.1em;">
            [% IF phase1.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSIF phase1.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
            Phase 1: Database Schema & Models ([% phase1.status %])
        </summary>
        <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <p><strong>What:</strong> Create/extend DBIx::Class Result classes for workshop data model. Schema system auto-generates database tables and columns.</p>
            <p><strong>Why:</strong> Schema-driven approach ensures type safety, relationship integrity, and automatic migration. This phase establishes the data foundation for all workshop functionality including lifecycle management, multi-site support, participant tracking, content management, email history, and role-based access.</p>
            <p><strong>Key Tasks:</strong> Extend WorkShop.pm and Participant.pm (add new columns, relationships, custom methods). Create WorkshopContent.pm, WorkshopEmail.pm, WorkshopRole.pm, SiteWorkshop.pm. Update Schema/Ency.pm to register new Result classes.</p>
            
            <div style="margin: 10px 0; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background: white;">
                <h5>📊 Database Project Details</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Project ID:</strong> [% phase1.id %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Status:</strong> [% phase1.status %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> [% phase1.start_date %] → [% phase1.end_date %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Estimated Hours:</strong> [% phase1.estimated_man_hours %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Project Code:</strong> [% phase1.project_code %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Description:</strong> [% phase1.description %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Comments:</strong> [% phase1.comments %]</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <a href="/project/details?project_id=[% phase1.id %]" target="_blank">View Details</a> |
                    <a href="/project/editproject?project_id=[% phase1.id %]" target="_blank">Edit</a> |
                    <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase1.id %]" target="_blank">Add Todo</a>
                </p>
                
                [% SET phase1_todos = phase1.todos.search({}, { order_by => 'sort_order' }) %]
                [% IF phase1_todos.count > 0 %]
                    <h6>📋 Todos ([% phase1_todos.count %]):</h6>
                    <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                        [% FOREACH task IN phase1_todos.all %]
                            <li style="margin: 5px 0; padding: 5px; border-left: 2px solid #FF9800; background: #fafafa;">
                                [% IF task.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSIF task.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
                                [% task.subject %]
                                <br><small>Status: [% task.status %] | Due: [% task.due_date %]</small>
                                <br><a href="/todo/showtodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">View</a> |
                                <a href="/todo/edittodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">Edit</a>
                            </li>
                        [% END %]
                    </ul>
                [% ELSE %]
                    <p><em>No todos. <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase1.id %]">Add a todo</a></em></p>
                [% END %]
            </div>
        </div>
    </details>
    [% END %]
    
    <!-- Phases 2-8: Abbreviated version to stay within character limits -->
    [% FOR phase_id IN [176..182] %]
        [% SET phase = schema.resultset('Project').find(phase_id) %]
        [% IF phase %]
        <details class="phase-container" style="margin: 15px 0; border: 2px solid #2196F3; padding: 10px; background: #e3f2fd;">
            <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.1em;">
                [% IF phase.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSIF phase.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
                [% phase.name %] ([% phase.status %])
            </summary>
            <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
                <p><strong>Description:</strong> [% phase.description %]</p>
                
                <div style="margin: 10px 0; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background: white;">
                    <h5>📊 Database Project Details</h5>
                    <ul>
                        <li><strong>Project ID:</strong> [% phase.id %]</li>
                        <li><strong>Status:</strong> [% phase.status %]</li>
                        <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> [% phase.start_date %] → [% phase.end_date %]</li>
                        <li><strong>Estimated Hours:</strong> [% phase.estimated_man_hours %]</li>
                        <li><strong>Project Code:</strong> [% phase.project_code %]</li>
                        <li><strong>Comments:</strong> [% phase.comments %]</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>
                        <a href="/project/details?project_id=[% phase.id %]" target="_blank">View Details</a> |
                        <a href="/project/editproject?project_id=[% phase.id %]" target="_blank">Edit</a> |
                        <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase.id %]" target="_blank">Add Todo</a>
                    </p>
                    
                    [% SET phase_todos = phase.todos.search({}, { order_by => 'sort_order' }) %]
                    [% IF phase_todos.count > 0 %]
                        <h6>📋 Todos ([% phase_todos.count %]):</h6>
                        <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                            [% FOREACH task IN phase_todos.all %]
                                <li style="margin: 5px 0; padding: 5px; border-left: 2px solid #2196F3; background: #fafafa;">
                                    [% IF task.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSIF task.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
                                    [% task.subject %]
                                    <br><small>Status: [% task.status %] | Due: [% task.due_date %]</small>
                                    <br><a href="/todo/showtodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">View</a> |
                                    <a href="/todo/edittodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">Edit</a>
                                </li>
                            [% END %]
                        </ul>
                    [% ELSE %]
                        <p><em>No todos. <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase.id %]">Add a todo</a></em></p>
                    [% END %]
                </div>
            </div>
        </details>
        [% END %]
    [% END %]
    
    <!-- Phase 9: Enhanced Features & Documentation -->
    [% SET phase9 = schema.resultset('Project').find(183) %]
    [% IF phase9 %]
    <details class="phase-container" style="margin: 15px 0; border: 2px solid #9C27B0; padding: 10px; background: #f3e5f5;">
        <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.1em;">
            [% IF phase9.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSIF phase9.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
            Phase 9: Enhanced Features & Documentation ([% phase9.status %])
        </summary>
        <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <p><strong>What:</strong> Implement enhanced file access for past workshops, mailing list management, email opt-out functionality, and comprehensive workshop leader tutorials.</p>
            <p><strong>Why:</strong> Workshop leaders need flexible tools to manage communications with attendees who registered offline, create custom mailing lists, and respect participant email preferences. Comprehensive tutorials ensure workshop leaders can effectively use all system features.</p>
            <p><strong>Key Tasks:</strong> Update file download authorization for past participants, add registration_method field to participants, create mailing list management system, implement opt-out/unsubscribe functionality with tokens, create comprehensive WorkShopLeaderGuide.tt tutorial.</p>
            
            <div style="margin: 10px 0; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #ddd; background: white;">
                <h5>📊 Database Project Details</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Project ID:</strong> [% phase9.id %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Status:</strong> [% phase9.status %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Timeline:</strong> [% phase9.start_date %] → [% phase9.end_date %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Estimated Hours:</strong> [% phase9.estimated_man_hours %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Project Code:</strong> [% phase9.project_code %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Description:</strong> [% phase9.description %]</li>
                    <li><strong>Comments:</strong> [% phase9.comments %]</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    <a href="/project/details?project_id=[% phase9.id %]" target="_blank">View Details</a> |
                    <a href="/project/editproject?project_id=[% phase9.id %]" target="_blank">Edit</a> |
                    <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase9.id %]" target="_blank">Add Todo</a>
                </p>
                
                [% SET phase9_todos = phase9.todos.search({}, { order_by => 'sort_order' }) %]
                [% IF phase9_todos.count > 0 %]
                    <h6>📋 Todos ([% phase9_todos.count %]):</h6>
                    <ul style="list-style-type: none; padding-left: 0;">
                        [% FOREACH task IN phase9_todos.all %]
                            <li style="margin: 5px 0; padding: 5px; border-left: 2px solid #9C27B0; background: #fafafa;">
                                [% IF task.status == 'In-Process' %]⏳[% ELSIF task.status == 'Completed' %]✅[% ELSE %]📌[% END %]
                                [% task.subject %]
                                <br><small>Status: [% task.status %] | Due: [% task.due_date %]</small>
                                <br><a href="/todo/showtodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">View</a> |
                                <a href="/todo/edittodo?record_id=[% task.record_id %]" target="_blank" style="font-size: 0.9em;">Edit</a>
                            </li>
                        [% END %]
                    </ul>
                [% ELSE %]
                    <p><em>No todos. <a href="/todo/addtodo?project_id=[% phase9.id %]">Add a todo</a></em></p>
                [% END %]
            </div>
            
            <div style="margin: 10px 0; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #9C27B0; background: #fce4ec;">
                <h5>🎯 Key Enhancements</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>File Access:</strong> Allow past workshop attendees to download files from workshops they completed</li>
                    <li><strong>Mailing Lists:</strong> Create custom recipient groups, send to individuals or groups, track registration method (online/manual/imported)</li>
                    <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe links in all emails, token-based unsubscribe mechanism, email preference management</li>
                    <li><strong>Tutorial:</strong> Comprehensive guide covering all features (creation, lifecycle, participants, files, content, emails, multi-site)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </details>
    [% ELSE %]
    <details class="phase-container" style="margin: 15px 0; border: 2px solid #9C27B0; padding: 10px; background: #f3e5f5;">
        <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: bold; font-size: 1.1em;">
            📌 Phase 9: Enhanced Features & Documentation (Not Yet in Database)
        </summary>
        <div style="margin-top: 10px;">
            <p><strong>Status:</strong> <span style="background: #fff3cd; padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px;">Project not yet created in database (Project ID 183)</span></p>
            <p><strong>What:</strong> Implement enhanced file access for past workshops, mailing list management, email opt-out functionality, and comprehensive workshop leader tutorials.</p>
            <p><strong>Why:</strong> Workshop leaders need flexible tools to manage communications with attendees who registered offline, create custom mailing lists, and respect participant email preferences. Comprehensive tutorials ensure workshop leaders can effectively use all system features.</p>
            <p><strong>Key Tasks:</strong> Update file download authorization for past participants, add registration_method field to participants, create mailing list management system, implement opt-out/unsubscribe functionality with tokens, create comprehensive WorkShopLeaderGuide.tt tutorial.</p>
            <p><a href="/project/addproject" target="_blank">Create Project in Database</a></p>
            
            <div style="margin: 10px 0; padding: 10px; border: 1px solid #9C27B0; background: #fce4ec;">
                <h5>🎯 Key Enhancements</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>File Access:</strong> Allow past workshop attendees to download files from workshops they completed</li>
                    <li><strong>Mailing Lists:</strong> Create custom recipient groups, send to individuals or groups, track registration method (online/manual/imported)</li>
                    <li><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> Unsubscribe links in all emails, token-based unsubscribe mechanism, email preference management</li>
                    <li><strong>Tutorial:</strong> Comprehensive guide covering all features (creation, lifecycle, participants, files, content, emails, multi-site)</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </details>
    [% END %]
    
[% CATCH %]
    <p style="color: #d9534f;"><strong>Error loading phase details:</strong> [% error.info %]</p>
[% END %]
